						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the east verandah of the Bhramarēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Pramādi, Māgha, ba. 11.</p>						

						<p>Seems to record the erection of a flag-staff pillar in the temple of Bhramarēśvara and also gift of land for conducting services by Vīrappa, son of Sāni Sadāsiva.</p>						

						</summary>
